{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"edcabbe5-157f-4c2c-99b0-3fc463cec70d","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter editing, run:\n```bash\ndotnet --version        # confirm SDK 11.0.100\ndotnet build            # verify it compiles\ndotnet test             # run your tests\n```\n\nAlso review the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fe0518ae-e4f6-4770-aed2-8e581da41598","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":323,"requestId":"2839:1007E7:15DB7E2:1885C92:6A0285E5"},"id":"11b694ec-0f35-4538-aac1-6fd4855f6ac9","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:44:13.711Z","parentId":"4fbf6b2c-0a54-47e6-ba4f-9ece604b1d26"}
